org.dgfoundation.amp.ar

Class Viewable

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dgfoundation.amp.ar.Viewable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Cell, Column, ReportData

    public abstract class Viewable
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    Class describing a viewable behaviour. Viewable objects always have a viewer name for each view modes (types). A viewer is responsible for showing the contents of the cell to the end user. One type of cell can have many viewers, depending on the number of export formats that we require (html,cvs,xls,pdf,etc...)
    Since:
    Jun 23, 2006

        public abstract int getVisibleRows()
        required by : pagination implemented by each subclass to return the number of rows that are displayed for this item. example. each amount cell should display one row. a groupReportData would display more rows - the title of the hierarchy + the totals row = 2 rows

        the number of rows actively used on the screen to render this object
